Replace systemd/logind bits with their FreeBSD equivalents.

There are two independent changes here:

  resources/niri.desktop: point the session entry at `niri --session`
  instead of the `niri-session` wrapper. That wrapper is a shell script
  that coordinates with systemd user units and is not useful on FreeBSD.

  src/niri.rs: redirect the power-key Inhibit D-Bus call from
  org.freedesktop.login1 (systemd-logind) to org.freedesktop.ConsoleKit
  (ConsoleKit2). The session lock calls elsewhere in niri.rs use
  logind-zbus which is still fine to leave alone; only this one call is
  done manually and needs retargeting.

Adapted from the FreeBSD ports tree (x11-wm/niri files/patch-no-systemd).

--- a/resources/niri.desktop
+++ b/resources/niri.desktop
@@ -1,6 +1,6 @@
 [Desktop Entry]
 Name=Niri
 Comment=A scrollable-tiling Wayland compositor
-Exec=niri-session
+Exec=niri --session
 Type=Application
 DesktopNames=niri
--- a/src/niri.rs
+++ b/src/niri.rs
@@ -2596,9 +2596,9 @@

         let message = conn.call_method(
-            Some("org.freedesktop.login1"),
-            "/org/freedesktop/login1",
-            Some("org.freedesktop.login1.Manager"),
+            Some("org.freedesktop.ConsoleKit"),
+            "/org/freedesktop/ConsoleKit/Manager",
+            Some("org.freedesktop.ConsoleKit.Manager"),
             "Inhibit",
             &("handle-power-key", "niri", "Power key handling", "block"),
         )?;
